sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    box rgb(235, 235, 235) USER
        participant U as Browser
    end
    box rgb(214, 232, 255) OUR MAIN SERVER - the API process that dispatches and long-polls results back
        participant API as API route<br/>(WorkflowRuns.ts)
    end
    box rgb(240, 240, 218) TEMPORAL CLOUD - their machines. Durable history, queues, timers, retries. Runs NONE of our code, never touches our DB
        participant TC as Temporal Cloud
    end
    box rgb(255, 228, 209) OUR TEMPORAL WORKER - runs workflow sandbox + activities. May be the same physical box as the API (GRAPHFLOW_EMBED_WORKER=1)
        participant WF as Workflow sandbox<br/>(GraphflowRun / Ctx)
        participant ACT as Activities<br/>(memo_lookup, run_engine_node, ...)
    end
    box rgb(220, 244, 220) OUR DISK
        participant DB as SQLite ledger +<br/>payload files
    end

    U->>API: POST /workflow-runs/42/execute
    API->>DB: read workspace 42 + user attachments (the snapshot)
    API->>TC: gRPC: describe wfrun-abc-42 (open run? snapshot changed? supersede?)
    API->>TC: gRPC: workflow.start("GraphflowRun", id=wfrun-abc-42, queue=q, USE_EXISTING)
    Note over TC: execution durably recorded.<br/>Nothing of ours has executed yet.
    API-->>U: 202 { temporal_workflow_id }
    Note over API: our main server is DONE dispatching.<br/>From here it only long-polls results back (SSE pump, bottom).

    WF->>TC: worker long-polls queue q
    TC-->>WF: WORKFLOW task
    Note over WF: >>> our WORKFLOW code begins here <<<<br/>GraphflowRun(inp) - deterministic jail: no I/O, no DB, no clock.<br/>ctx.node(): validate args, null-fill absent params,<br/>encode artifacts as {$artifact: content-hash},<br/>memo_key = sha256(node identity + canonical-args hash) - pure JS.
    WF->>TC: await memo_lookup(...) is NOT a call:<br/>emits ScheduleActivity command, workflow PARKS
    TC-->>ACT: ACTIVITY task memo_lookup (via worker long-poll)
    Note over ACT: >>> our ACTIVITY code begins here <<<
    ACT->>DB: SELECT ... WHERE engagement_id=? AND memo_key=?  (check #1's read)
    DB-->>ACT: ref or null
    ACT-->>TC: result appended to durable history
    TC-->>WF: WORKFLOW task - resume at the awaited line<br/>(warm in memory, or REPLAY from history: same state either way)

    alt CACHE HIT
        WF->>TC: schedule attach_artifact - parks
        TC-->>ACT: activity task
        ACT->>DB: INSERT workspace membership ... ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING
        ACT-->>TC: done
        TC-->>WF: resume: memo_hits.push(node). NODE BODY NEVER RAN.
    else CACHE MISS - engine node
        WF->>TC: schedule run_engine_node(NodeRequest) - parks
        TC-->>ACT: activity task
        ACT->>DB: memoLookup again (check #2: activity-retry guard)
        ACT->>DB: read input payloads from storage
        Note over ACT: def.run(args) - THE NODE BODY.<br/>The only place it ever executes.
        ACT->>DB: recordCompletion: BEGIN IMMEDIATE, memo check #3,<br/>INSERT artifact (ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING),<br/>INSERT node_run + node_run_inputs, attach, COMMIT.<br/>UNIQUE(engagement, memo_key) is the final tiebreak.
        ACT-->>TC: { ref, fresh: true }
        TC-->>WF: resume: executed.push(node)
    else CACHE MISS - human node
        WF->>TC: schedule ensure_human_task - parks
        TC-->>ACT: activity task
        ACT->>TC: workflow.start("GraphflowHumanTask", id=node-abc-7-memoKey, USE_EXISTING)
        ACT-->>TC: task workflow id
        loop until a reviewer answers (the answer lands via record_human_completion -> same recordCompletion)
            WF->>TC: await sleep(1s -> 30s cap): a DURABLE TIMER in Temporal Cloud,<br/>not a thread on our box - our machine may reboot meanwhile
            TC-->>WF: timer fired
            WF->>TC: schedule memo_lookup - parks
            TC-->>ACT: activity task
            ACT->>DB: SELECT by memo_key
            ACT-->>TC: ref or null
            TC-->>WF: resume
        end
    end

    Note over WF: ...repeat for every ctx.node() in the workflow walk...
    WF-->>TC: GraphflowRun returns Summary { executed, memo_hits, human_waits }
    Note over TC: the Summary lives ONLY in the execution result and history.<br/>It is never written to SQLite.

    loop every ~1s from the 202 until finished or failed
        API->>TC: gRPC: describe + query("progress")
        TC-->>API: status + live Summary snapshot
        API-->>U: SSE frame (progress / finished / failed)
    end
